File: South Africa has a sub-investment grade with all three major credit rating agencies. AFP/Emmanuel Dunand JOHANNESBURG - Two credit rating agencies, Moody's and S&P Global, will publish their latest ratings for South Africa on Friday night. There are fears the two agencies might further downgrade South Africa. READ: Moody’s lowers SA growth forecast Should that happen, the country will find the cost of borrowing money will increase. South Africa has a sub-investment grade with all three major credit rating agencies. This means they regard the country's ability to repay its debt as weak. READ: S&P keeps South Africa on junk status South Africa has failed to grow its economy in recent years. The COVID-19 pandemic has worsened the situation.